    <main>
      <h2>After the Shift</h2>

      <p>
	After the shift<br>
	I can quietly change<br>
	Gears into something<br>
	More confident
      </p>

      <p>
	In its own ability<br>
	To live freely<br>
	Unhindered by the pressures<br>
	Of clocks, and pumps
      </p>

      <p>
	And managers whose heads<br>
	Look like floating whale<br>
	Carcasses by the beach<br>
	But a great deal less
      </p>

      <p>
	Spectacular, and natural too<br>
	Than a dowager reaching<br>
	The end of her<br>
	Life on Earth
      </p>

      <p>
	As the heat dissipates<br>
	From the tired body<br>
	And the cool breeze<br>
	Rejoins the waiting sea;
      </p>

      <p>
	This, a seasonal change<br>
	And a time for being slow<br>
	In a soothing arm<br>
	Where the water will flow.
      </p>
      
    </main>
